Terraform AWS S3 Static Website with CloudFront
This Terraform project provisions an AWS S3 bucket configured as a static website, fronted by a CloudFront CDN for global distribution with HTTPS.

Features
âœ… S3 Bucket â€“ Hosts static website files (HTML, CSS, JS)
âœ… CloudFront CDN â€“ Provides fast, secure global delivery
âœ… Origin Access Identity (OAI) â€“ Secures S3 access via CloudFront only
âœ… HTTPS Enabled â€“ Uses CloudFrontâ€™s default SSL certificate
âœ… Default Root Object â€“ Automatically serves index.html

Prerequisites
Before deploying, ensure you have:

AWS CLI configured with credentials (aws configure)

Terraform installed (Download Here)

A globally unique S3 bucket name (update in main.tf)

Deployment Steps
1. Clone the Repository
sh
git clone https://github.com/your-repo/terraform-s3-cloudfront.git
cd terraform-s3-cloudfront
2. Initialize Terraform
sh
terraform init
3. Review & Apply Changes
sh
terraform plan  # Preview changes
terraform apply # Deploy infrastructure
Note: CloudFront deployment may take 5-10 minutes.

4. Upload Website Files
sh
aws s3 cp index.html s3://your-bucket-name/
Replace index.html with your website files.

Accessing Your Website
CloudFront URL:
https://<distribution-id>.cloudfront.net
(Find distribution-id in AWS Console or terraform output)

S3 Website Endpoint (Unsecured):
http://your-bucket-name.s3-website-us-east-1.amazonaws.com

Terraform Outputs
After deployment, Terraform will display:

CloudFront Domain â€“ The HTTPS-enabled CDN URL

S3 Bucket Name â€“ Your static website bucket

Example:

sh
Outputs:
cloudfront_domain = "d123.cloudfront.net"
s3_bucket_name = "my-unique-s3-website-bucket"
Cleaning Up
To destroy all resources:

sh
terraform destroy
Warning: This will permanently delete your S3 bucket and CloudFront distribution.

Troubleshooting
Issue	Solution
Access BentSet error	Verify S3 bucket policy allows CloudFront OAI
CloudFront returns 403	Ensure index.html exists in S3
Changes not reflecting?	Create a CloudFront invalidation (/*)
